  <meta name="DC.date.created" content="2016-06-16T09:54:03+11:00" scheme="W3CDTF" />
  <meta name="DC.date.modified" content="2016-07-06T09:54:03+11:00" scheme="W3CDTF" />

  <meta content="" name="flags" />
  <meta content="This test checks that if color inversion on the pixels on the screen is supported by the user agent, then 'outline-color: invert' in this test should render a filled black square otherwise, if color inversion on the pixels on the screen is not supported by the user agent, then 'outline-color: invert' in this test should compute to the computed color value of the element ('currentColor' in CSS3 ui) which is orange in which case a filled orange square should be rendered. That same logic should prevail in both shorthand form and longhand form." name="assert" />

  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
  div#parent
    {
      background-color: white;
      padding: 50px;
      width: 0px;
    }

  div#child
    {
      color: orange;
      outline: invert solid 50px; /* shorthand form, shorthand declaration */
      width: 0px;
    }
  ]]></style>

 </head>

 <body>

  <p>Test passes if there is a filled orange square or a filled black square.</p>

  <div id="parent">
    <div id="child"></div>
  </div>

 </body>
</html>